  "text": "Despite its theoretical importance, the free viewing design of this experiment may also have shortcomings given that the possible differences in the motivational states of each species may have had certain influence on the results (although we did not find any behavioral evidence to show such motivational differences). We also recognize that genuine natural patterns of gaze movements can be observed only during the course of daily activities. Thus, further studies simulating naturalistic contexts (e.g., use of headmounted eye-tracking devices) [CITATION_1] are necessary.",
